chosen.content:
Track consecutive failures with a counter and only escalate the message after a few in a row, so a single dropped read doesn't flash an alarming message unnecessarily, while the loop keeps running normally and keeps retrying:

```cpp
int failCount = 0;
...
if (isnan(h) || isnan(t)) {
  failCount++;
  lcd.clear();
  lcd.setCursor(0, 0);
  lcd.print(failCount > 3 ? "Check Wiring!" : "Sensor Error");
} else {
  failCount = 0;
  ...
}
```

